         <span class="mi">x</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <span class="mo">−</span>
      <span class="mi">z</span>
     </div>
     <span class="mo">)</span>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>, where 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="i75" class="math">
    <div class="msub">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">M</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <div mathvariant="italic" class="mstyle">
       <span class="mi">m</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <span class="mi">x</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> is the maximum melt rate that occurs at a depth 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="i76" class="math">
    <div class="msub">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">z</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <div mathvariant="italic" class="mstyle">
       <span class="mi">m</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <span class="mi">x</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>. Perturbations in 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="i77" class="math">
    <div class="msub">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">M</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <div mathvariant="italic" class="mstyle">
       <span class="mi">m</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <span class="mi">x</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> are varied every month and renormalized to ensure that the SD of monthly 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="i78" class="math">
    <div class="msub">
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mi">M</span>
     </div>
     <div class="mrow">
      <div mathvariant="italic" class="mstyle">
       <span class="mi">m</span>
       <span class="mi">a</span>
       <span class="mi">x</span>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> is always 5 m/y, regardless of the long-term persistence. Surface mass balance and surface temperatures averaged over the 1979 to 2010 period from RACMO2 (
  <a rid="r39" ref-type="bibr" href="#r39">39</a>) are applied at the surface of the domain and held constant in time.
 </p>
